passive bishop on g7.}) 20... b4 21. Nc4 Bb5 22. Rac1 $16 {and White is in
control.}) 14... Qa5 (14... Bxg4 $6 {[#] is a thematic and practically
interesting sacrifice that is, however, refuted by the cold calculation:} 15.
fxg4 Nxg4 {and now, White can force the queen trade with} 16. Bxc5 $1 $146 (16.
h5 Qb6 (16... Nxe3 $142 17. Qxe3 Bf6 $16 {would have made more sense for Black,
with some compensation on the dark squares.}) 17. h6 Bf6 18. Bg1 Bd8 19. Be2
Nf6 20. Rc1 $18 {Anton Guijarro-Popovic,D, Batumi 2018}) 16... dxc5 17. Qg5 Qb6
18. Be2 $1 Qxb2 19. Qc1 $1 Qxc1+ 20. Rxc1 $18 {leaving Black in a pretty
hopeless endgame.}) 15. h5 {[#] We have reached the critical position. Both
sides have made progress on opposite sides of the board, and the ball in in
Black's court. In practice, two moves have been tried, but Black has two more
options worth investigating.} a3 {This natural move unexpectedly runs into a
near-refutation.} ({I believe that the best way for Black to develop
counterplay is} 15... b5 $5 $146 {[#] although this move has not been tried in
practice. According to my analysis, White can get an edge with two moves:} {1)}
16. h6 ({and 2)} 16. Rd1 b4 17. Nb1 a3 18. Nxa3 $1 Ncxe4 $1 19. fxe4 bxa3 20.
Qxa5 Rxa5 21. b4 $14 {the endgame is complex, but White has a passed pawn and
better-placed pieces.}) 16... Bh8 17. Nf5 $1 {This is a motive from the main
line.} Bxf5 18. gxf5 b4 19. Nd1 Nfd7 20. Bh3 Bf6 21. O-O $14 {and, while Black
has managed to save his dark-squared bishop from imprisonment on h8, White's
position should still be for preference.}) ({Once again, the piece sacrifice:} 
15... Bxg4 $6 16. fxg4 Nxg4 {as played in Livaic-Srbis, Biograd na Moru 2018,
can be refuted. This time by the precise:} 17. Bg5 $146 f6 18. Bh3 $1 fxg5 19.
Bxg4 $18) (15... Rfc8 {avoids variations where his bishop gets stuck on h8,
but Black is just too slow with his counterplay. After:} 16. hxg6 fxg6 17. g5
Ne8 {White can go all-in with:} 18. Qh2 $1 a3 19. b4 $1 Qxb4 20. Qxh7+ Kf7 21.
Bd2 Qb2 22. Rb1 Na4 $5 {This is a very interesting tactical resource, but it
does not quite work:} 23. Rxb2 axb2 24. Nb1 $1 Rc1+ 25. Kf2 Rxb1 26. Bd3 Rxh1
27. Qxh1 $18 {and White should be winning here.}) 16. b4 $1 {This strong pawn
sacrifice gives White a huge initiative.} Qxb4 17. Rb1 Qa5 18. h6 Bh8 {[#]} 19.
Nf5 $1 {Threatening no less than a checkmate on e7!} Bxf5 20. gxf5 Nfd7 $2 {
A decisive mistake.} ({Much more stubborn would have been} 20... Ne8 {but
White still has a great position after} 21. Nb5 $16) 21. Nb5 Qb6 {and now in
the game Kashlinskaya, A-Guichard, P, Antalya 2019, 1-0 (22), White would have
obtained a winning position immediately with} 22. fxg6 fxg6 23. Bh3 $18 *

