) 13... Bd7 {Playing for ...b7-b5 is the best.} ({In majority of games in this
line, Black have preferred} 13... a4 {but after} 14. h4 Bd7 15. h5 {[#]
White's pawn storm on the kingside is already quicker than Black's queenside
play. White can even play positionally in many variations, preventing
Black's counterplay and counting on his space advantage in the long run. Below
is the overview of current theoretical material:} Rb8 (15... Rc8 16. Kf1 $1 {
Evacuating the king from the centre} a3 17. b3 Qa5 18. Rc1 ({Maybe even more
practical was} 18. Nb5 $5 Qxd2 19. Bxd2 Bxb5 20. Bxb5 $18 {leading into a
