21. Bh6 $40 {and White had a winning attack in Caruana-Nakamura, London 2018.})
(15... a3 16. bxa3 ({There is also nothing wrong with} 16. b3 $5 Qa5 17. Rc1
Rfc8 18. Kf1 $16 {though the text is simpler.}) 16... Qa5 {½-½ (91)
Raghunandan, K (2442)-Priasmoro, N (2457) Yogyakarta INA 2019} (16... f6 17. hxg6
hxg6 18. Rb1 Kf7 19. Nb5 Qe7 20. Kf1 Rh8 21. Kg2 $16 {1-0 (67) Zhou,J (2584)
-Abdulwahhab, A (2219) Hamedan 2018}) 17. O-O $146 Rfc8 18. Rfc1 Qxa3 19. Rab1
$16) 16. Rc1 $5 $146 (16. Kf1 b5 17. Kg2 b4 18. Nd1 Nc7 19. Bh6 Bf6 $5 (19...
Qe7 $1 $11) 20. f3 Bb5 21. Nf2 Bxe2 22. Nxe2 b3 23. a3 Nb5 24. Rh2 $40 {
1-0 (78) Iturrizaga,E (2637)-Amonatov,F (2624) Bhubaneswar IND 2019}) 16... b5
17. f3 b4 18. Nd1 $16 {White just has a solid positional advantage in most of
these lines since Black lacks any good plan, while he can gradually improve
his position on the kingside.}) 14. h4 {[#]} (14. Nb5 $5 {is a playable
alternative, similar to Anton Guijarro's game from Chapter 1. White is trying
to prevent knight manoeuvre from the main line. However, Black can still
