16. Nd1 b4 $1 {[#] This is the real point of Black's play. He is ready to
sacrifice a pawn to speed up his counterplay with ...Nc7-b5-d4.} ({
It would be too slow to play} 16... N7a6 17. h5 Qe7 18. f3 $16 {with a similar
